    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes optional mechanisms for using directory
   server(s) to assist TRILL (Transparent Interconnection of Lots of
   Links) edge switches in reducing multi-destination traffic,
   particularly ARP/ND and unknown unicast flooding.</t>
